issues.title: Turbocharger Failure
issues.description: The Garrett T03/T04 turbocharger is prone to bearing failure, oil seal leakage, and compressor wheel damage, especially in modified vehicles or those with poor maintenance history.
symptoms: Blue or white smoke from exhaust
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger with rebuilt or new unit, inspect oil supply and drain lines, replace oil and filter
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with quality oil, proper warm-up and cool-down procedures, avoid excessive boost modifications

issues.title: Transmission Overdrive Unit Failure
issues.description: The 200-4R transmission's overdrive unit is weak and prone to failure, causing loss of overdrive gear, harsh shifting, or complete transmission failure.
issues.fix_description: Rebuild transmission with upgraded overdrive components, install shift kit and cooler
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, install auxiliary cooler, avoid aggressive driving

issues.title: Engine Knock Sensor Problems
issues.description: The knock sensor system is critical for preventing detonation but frequently fails, leading to false knock retard and reduced performance or engine damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace knock sensor, check wiring harness, update ECM programming if available
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, maintain proper tune, protect sensor wiring from heat damage

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock
issues.description: Hot restart problems and stalling due to fuel vaporization in the fuel rails and lines, especially common in hot weather conditions.
symptoms: Engine dying at idle when hot
issues.fix_description: Install fuel rail insulation, upgrade fuel lines, add return line modifications, relocate fuel filter
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank full in hot weather, park in shade when possible, maintain proper fuel pressure

issues.title: Mass Air Flow Sensor Failure
issues.description: The MAF sensor becomes contaminated or fails, causing incorrect air/fuel mixture calculations and poor engine performance.
issues.fix_description: Clean or replace MAF sensor, inspect air filter and intake system for leaks
issues.prevention: Regular air filter replacement, avoid oiled air filters, keep intake system clean

issues.title: Intercooler Brick Failure
issues.description: The plastic intercooler end tanks crack or the core develops internal blockages, reducing cooling efficiency and boost pressure.
issues.fix_description: Replace intercooler with upgraded unit, pressure test all boost connections
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, monitor boost pressure, avoid excessive boost levels

issues.title: Rear End Housing Cracking
issues.description: The 8.5-inch rear differential housing develops cracks around the pinion area due to high torque loads, especially in modified vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace rear differential housing, upgrade to stronger aftermarket unit if available
issues.prevention: Avoid excessive torque modifications, regular differential service, proper launch technique

issues.title: Fuel Pump Hot Tank Problems
issues.description: The in-tank fuel pump overheats and fails prematurely, especially when fuel levels are low or in hot weather conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump with high-pressure unit, install fuel pump hotwire kit
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, use quality fuel, maintain proper electrical connections

issues.title: Oil Pan Gasket Leakage
issues.description: The oil pan gasket frequently develops leaks due to engine heat cycles and torque, causing oil spots and potential engine damage if ignored.
issues.fix_description: Replace oil pan gasket, clean mating surfaces thoroughly, torque to specification
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, monitor oil levels, avoid over-tightening drain plug

issues.title: ECM Capacitor Failure
issues.description: The electrolytic capacitors in the ECM fail over time, causing erratic engine behavior, loss of memory, and intermittent running issues.
issues.fix_description: Rebuild ECM with new capacitors or replace with remanufactured unit
issues.prevention: Protect ECM from heat and moisture, maintain clean electrical connections

issues.title: Brake Master Cylinder Failure
issues.description: The brake master cylinder develops internal seepage, causing brake fade, soft pedal feel, and potential brake failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake master cylinder, bleed entire brake system, inspect brake lines
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, monitor fluid level, replace fluid every 2-3 years

issues.title: Chassis Wiring Harness Degradation
issues.description: The engine and chassis wiring harnesses deteriorate due to heat and age, causing multiple electrical issues and intermittent problems.
issues.fix_description: Replace affected wiring sections, upgrade to modern wire types, protect from heat sources
issues.prevention: Inspect wiring regularly, protect from heat and abrasion, use quality electrical connections

editorial.tagline: Darth Vader's muscle car: turbocharged terror in disguise
editorial.hero_blurb: The Grand National stands as GM's most menacing muscle car, wrapped in sinister black paint and powered by a boosted V6 that embarrassed V8s twice its size. This is American performance engineering at its most unexpected and effective.
editorial.essence: The Grand National proved that displacement isn't everything, using forced induction to extract shocking power from a modest 3.8L V6. It's the anti-Corvette: understated menace that delivers knockout performance wrapped in luxury car comfort.
editorial.heritage: Born from Buick's NASCAR success in the early 1980s, the Grand National honored the brand's racing heritage while showcasing GM's turbocharging prowess. The final 1987 GNX became an instant legend, marking the end of the original muscle car era.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers focused on maximum impact through subtlety - blacked-out aesthetics, functional aerodynamics, and sophisticated turbocharging created a sleeper that could outrun Corvettes while maintaining luxury car refinement.
editorial.motorsport_history: Named after Buick's dominance in NASCAR's Grand National series, where the brand won championships in 1981 and 1982. The street car channeled that racing success into a production vehicle that proved turbocharging's potential.
editorial.engine_character: The turbocharged 3.8L delivers a unique punch - smooth at cruise, then explosive when the boost builds. It's an engine that rewards patience with devastating mid-range torque delivery that pins you to the seat.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 4-speed automatic prioritizes power delivery over engagement, with firm shifts under boost and smooth operation during normal driving. It's tuned for maximum acceleration rather than sporting character.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Built on GM's G-body platform, it offers composed highway cruising with surprising cornering ability for its size. The suspension balances comfort with controlled body motion, though it's clearly optimized for straight-line performance.
editorial.steering_feel: Recirculating ball steering provides adequate feedback with reasonable weight, typical of 1980s American cars. It's precise enough for spirited driving but won't be mistaken for a sports car.
editorial.brake_confidence: Four-wheel disc brakes offer strong, progressive stopping power that matches the engine's performance. They provide confident deceleration from high speeds with good pedal feel and fade resistance.
editorial.sound_signature: The exhaust produces a distinctive whoosh-growl combination, with turbo whistle under acceleration and a deep, authoritative rumble at idle. It's unmistakably different from traditional V8 muscle cars.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance enthusiasts who appreciate understated menace, collectors seeking an iconic piece of 1980s Americana, and anyone who values unique character over conventional muscle car aesthetics.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking razor-sharp handling, manual transmission purists, or buyers wanting flashy exterior styling that announces performance intentions.
editorial.buyers_summary: Prices reflect the Grand National's legend status, with clean examples commanding premium dollars. Focus on maintenance records and original components, as these cars are becoming increasingly valuable and difficult to restore authentically.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
